      "stopReason": "end_turn",
      "agentSubtype": "success",
      "agentResultText": "\n\nThis is already implemented. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts:23-31` checks for a session on `/dashboard` and `/settings` and redirects unauthenticated users to `/auth/login`:\n\n```typescript\nconst protectedPaths = [\"/dashboard\", \"/settings\"];\nconst isProtected = protectedPaths.some((path) => pathname.startsWith(path));\n\nif (isProtected) {\n  const session = await auth0.getSession();\n  if (!session) {\n    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL(\"/auth/login\", request.url));\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAdditionally, the server actions in both `dashboard/actions.ts` and `settings/actions.ts` call `getRequiredUser()`, which double-checks the session and redirects to login if missing — so even direct form submissions are protected.",
