      "agentResultText": "\n\nThe sign-out button is already in the layout header at `src/app/layout.tsx:56-58` — it shows for all authenticated users across every page:\n\n```tsx\n<Button variant=\"outline\" size=\"sm\" asChild>\n  <a href=\"/auth/logout\">Log out</a>\n</Button>\n```\n\nFor session expiry, the middleware already handles this — `auth0.getSession()` returns `null` for expired sessions, and unauthenticated users on protected routes get redirected to login. The `getRequiredUser()` helper in server actions also redirects if the session is gone.\n\nThe only gap is that if a session expires while a user is browsing, the layout might still show cached authenticated UI until the next server render. Let me add `dynamic = \"force-dynamic\"` isn't needed here since Auth0's middleware already runs on every request and the layout is a server component that re-renders on navigation.\n\nThis is fully functional as-is. No changes needed.",
